      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Structural alerts relevant to hERG**\n- **Cationic piperidine/piperidinium + multiple aromatics** is a well-known hERG risk pattern (many high-affinity blockers share this topology).\n- Not \u201cterfenadine-like\u201d in the strict sense (no diaryl + tertiary alcohol motif), but it matches the broader **basic center + aromatic wings** alert class.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:00:40.602612+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "46d996db",
      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR reasoning (why these features matter for hERG)\nhERG blockers often have:\n1) **A cationic center** that can form electrostatic interactions (commonly with residues in the pore region) and help anchor the ligand in the cavity.\n2) **Aromatic/hydrophobic surfaces** that make strong van der Waals/\u03c0 interactions with hydrophobic/aromatic residues lining the channel (notably the well-known aromatic region in the inner cavity).\n3) **Appropriate spacing/shape** so the basic N and aromatic groups can simultaneously engage key interaction regions.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:00:40.602634+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "f7339924",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "This molecule has:\n- **Permanent/strong cationic character** \u2192 increases likelihood of strong binding in the channel cavity.\n- **Multiple fused and pendant phenyl rings** \u2192 strong hydrophobic/\u03c0 binding potential.\n- **A relatively rigid aromatic system** (fused bicyclic + phenyl) combined with a **semi-rigid saturated ring** \u2192 often favorable for maintaining a binding-competent conformation (less entropic penalty than very floppy molecules).",
      "tool_name": null,
