    },
    {
      "step_id": "c41b6daa",
      "step_index": 5,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) Mechanistic basis (how it could block hERG)\nhERG blockade is typically via **binding in the inner cavity** accessible from the cytosolic side, stabilizing a non-conducting state and physically occluding K\u207a permeation.",
