      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "Mechanistically plausible interactions here:\n- The **protonated amine** can serve as an **electrostatic anchor** in the cavity and/or engage in cation\u2013\u03c0 interactions.\n- The **extended aromatic surface** (fused bicyclic + phenyl) can **stack/pack** against hydrophobic/aromatic residues lining the pore.\n- The overall **amphiphilic character** (charged head + hydrophobic body) is consistent with many known hERG binders that partition into membrane and access the channel cavity.",
