      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 4) 3D/conformation considerations (critical for hERG)\n- The molecule has **two stereocenters** in the saturated ring, so **3D orientation** of the protonated N relative to the aromatic system is constrained.\n- The aromatic system is **rigid**, and the saturated ring provides a **defined vector** from the cationic N toward the hydrophobic/aromatic region.\n- This architecture can plausibly place the **cationic center and aromatic bulk at a distance/geometry** compatible with the hERG cavity pharmacophore (many blockers have ~1\u20132 bond separation from N to an aromatic system and additional hydrophobe further out; this compound appears to satisfy that general spatial requirement).",
